The flood situation in Bangladesh is dire, with millions displaced and at least 40 reported deaths.
Major rivers are overflowing, inundating large areas and forcing evacuations.
The government and military are providing relief efforts, but the situation is expected to worsen in the coming days.
Landslides and heavy rains have also caused casualties in neighboring countries like Nepal.
International aid, including from the UK, is being mobilized to assist in the relief efforts.
The focus is on providing food, water, shelter, and medical aid to those affected by the devastating floods.
